# Cursor Rules for YourOra Waitlist Project

## Project Configuration
- Use pnpm as the package manager
- This project uses Supabase CLI instead of global MCP
- Use Supabase SSR for authentication (not the deprecated auth helpers)

## Supabase Configuration
- Use @supabase/supabase-js and @supabase/ssr packages
- Environment variables are in .env.local
- Use Supabase CLI for database operations
- Do not use global MCP Supabase tools in this project

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript
- Follow Next.js 14+ patterns
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer server components when possible

## Dependencies
- Always use pnpm for package management
- Supabase SSR for authentication
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS

## File Structure
- API routes in app/api/
- Components in components/
- Types in types/
- Environment variables in .env.local

## Important Notes
- Do not use global MCP Supabase tools
- Use Supabase CLI for database operations
- The deprecated @supabase/auth-helpers is not used
- Use @supabase/ssr for server-side rendering with Supabase

